        "intro": "If your parent struggles to cook or shop for groceries due to physical limitations or being homebound, they may qualify for daily meal delivery at home. This federally-funded program delivers one or more nutritionally balanced meals per day directly to your parent's door, including specialized meals for conditions like diabetes or heart failure.\n\nYour parent must be 60 or older and unable to prepare meals independently due to physical, mental, or cognitive limitations. There are no income limits — eligibility is based on need and whether your parent is homebound (has difficulty leaving home unassisted regularly). The program operates through local providers in each county, so availability and wait times vary by location.\n\nMeals are provided at no cost, though voluntary contributions are welcomed. Because this isn't a single statewide program, you'll need to contact your local Area Agency on Aging for assessment and enrollment. Staff will visit your parent's home to determine eligibility and dietary needs.",
